the [[i18n|$:/ext/modules/macros/i18n-macro.js]] macro aims to make it easier to translate some parts of your [[TiddlyWiki|https://tiddlywiki.com/static/TiddlyWiki.html]] beside $:/languages + `<<lingo>>` mechanism. It might be useful to translate extensions or tiddlers.

 `<<i18n>>`  parameters are

* `title` : the tiddler title (default current tiddler title)
* `domain` : the tiddler //domain// of the tiddler (default `$:`)
* `dico` : if set to `dico` will search //title// entry in the `domain`/i18n/`lg-LG` [[dictionary tiddler|https://tiddlywiki.com/static/DictionaryTiddlers.html]]
* `orig_lang` : the original language of the tiddler (default `en-GB`)
* `inline` : set to `true` force //inline// rendering (d√©fault `false`). For short text mainly.

So,

```
<<i18n "i18n macro" "$:/ext/modules/macros/i18n" "fr-FR">>
```
will call

# the [[$:/ext/modules/macros/i18n/i18n/lg-LG/i18n macro]] tiddler where lg-LG is the current TiddlyWiki [[$:/language]]
# if missing, the original language tiddler : [[$:/ext/modules/macros/i18n/i18n/fr-FR/i18n macro]]
# if missing an alert telling that original tiddler doesn't exist

When using `dico` version, the process is almost the same, but the macro will search ##`title` entry in a $:/ext/modules/macros/i18n/i18n/lg-LG dictionary tiddler (or ''fr-FR'' base language if not set). It's more convenient for short phrases or words only translation. For now if entry doesn't exist, you will have blank text...

For tiddlers using `<<i18n>>` links will appear on translated parts hover in order to make edition easier. For case //.2// two links will apper : one for adding missing translation, the other for original language edition.

See current [[i18n macro]], [[un tiddler sans traduction en-GB]] and [[a tiddler without original version]] as live examples. $:/SiteTitle and $:/SiteSubtitle are using the //dico// version, have a look to  $:/ControlPanel to get more.
